Additional Considerations:
In MongoDB, documents can store nested arrays and objects. If your data includes more complex structures, you might need additional tables or a different schema design.
Remember that MongoDB does not rely on SQL; instead, it employs JavaScript as the primary language for document manipulation, which facilitates interaction with the database using a familiar syntax2. However, when translating to SQL, we follow the relational model conventions. Feel free to ask if you have any further questions! ğŸ˜ŠğŸ”ğŸ“Š